author: seattlepi.com
title: Fire crews tackle 4 blazes in Auburn
text:
AUBURN, Wash. (AP) â€” Fire officials are investigating four separate fires that broke out Sunday night in the city of Auburn south of Seattle.
Valley Regional Fire Authority says no one was injured in the blazes, which were reported within a two-hour period.
The most serious fire burned two homes and displaced three people. A fire also damaged an empty duplex building, caused minor exterior wall damage to another building and burned a shop next to a home.
KOMO-TV reports that investigators say the fires are suspicious but they're looking into what caused them.
